<paragraph blockId="20.[151,1437,511,789]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541">
<collectionCode box="[199,251,583,609]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541">TYPE</collectionCode>
MATERIAL: Sundevall, in his original description (1850: 99) gave no indication that he had more than a single female at hand. However, Sundevall’s acquisition catalogue indicated that he had 
<specimenCount box="[1186,1347,619,645]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
that he identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[301,494,655,681]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cheniana">
<emphasis box="[301,494,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="541">Alauda cheniana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but he later changed his mind and decided that 
<specimenCount box="[1060,1215,655,681]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
belonged to a new undescribed species close to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[474,682,691,717]" class="Aves" family="Alaudidae" genus="Alauda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="20" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="conirostris">
<emphasis box="[474,682,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="541">Alauda conirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This specimen should be treated as the single specimen in the type series and is a 
<typeStatus box="[318,419,727,753]" pageId="20" pageNumber="541">holotype</typeStatus>
, catalogue number NRM 569768 [6453], a study skin of an adult female collected 
<date pageId="20" pageNumber="541" value="1843-07-12">12 July 1843</date>
. See comments below for a discussion on geographical origin.
</paragraph>
